SMS Share 2 - Print Text Messages

How to Print Text (SMS) and Multimedia (MMS) Messages from an Android Phone

Android is an operating system developed by Google and used on a variety of different tablet and smartphone devices. Like any phone you can send and receive text and multimedia messages. If for any reason, you'd like to print any of your texts - this article will demonstrate how to do that.

Steps

  1. Helpful?
    1
    Launch Google Play. Tap the Google Play icon on your home screen or app drawer to launch the app.
    • Alternatively, you can download the app from : https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gilapps.smsshare2 and skip to the 7th step in which you choose the conversation to share.
  2. Helpful?
    2
    Search for “SMS Share 2”
  3. Helpful?
    3
    Tap the app made by GilApps.
  4. Helpful?
    4
    Download and install the app. Tap on “Install” to start the installation process.
  5. Helpful?
    5
    Launch SMS Share. After installation, you can tap “Open” from its Google Play page.
    • Alternatively, you can look for the app in your app drawer.
  6. Helpful?
    6
    Grant all the requested permissions. Tap on "Allow" twice
    • In older devices the user will not be asked to grant permissions.
  7. Helpful?
    7
    Select a conversation (text message thread). This will be the thread you want to share to your e-mail.
  8. Helpful?
    8
    Choose the messages in the thread and share. Tick which messages in the thread you want shared. and then tap on "Share"
    • Pro version: If you check more than 4 messages you'll be requested to pay a symbolic price in order to purchase the full version.
    • Free version: If you want, you can still use the free version - Just print 4 messages at a time.
  9. Helpful?
    9
    Send the messages to your email. Select your email app at the bottom of the screen.
    • You can share with your Gmail account or any e-mail app of your preference.
  10. Helpful?
    10
    Open your e-mail account on your PC or Mac.
    • Select the thread that has been e-mailed to you.
    • Download the attacPrint the downloaded file.

Tips

  • If you’ve got a printing app that can connect with a wireless printer, you can skip the e-mailing part and just share it with that app to print it directly.o print it directly.
